üìå Problem Statement
Given a sorted array of integers (which may include negative numbers), return a new array containing the squares of each number, also sorted in non-decreasing order.

üîπ Input
**An array of integers array
The array is already sorted in non-decreasing order
Example Input
[-5, -4, -2, 1, 9, 12]

üîπ Output
A new array containing the squares of each element, sorted in non-decreasing order
Example Output
[1, 4, 16, 25, 81, 144]

üîπ Constraints (Typical)
1 ‚â§ len(array) ‚â§ 10^5
-10^4 ‚â§ array[i] ‚â§ 10^4

SOLUTION:

# Time = O(n) Space = O(n)
def sorted_squared(array):
    i = 0
    j = len(array) - 1
    new_array = [0] * len(array)
    for k in reversed(range(len(array))):
        sq_i = array[i]**2
        sq_j = array[j]** 2
        if sq_i > sq_j:
            new_array[k] = sq_i
            i += 1
        else:
            new_array[k] = sq_j
            j -= 1
    return new_array
print(sorted_squared([-5,-4,-2, 1, 9,12]))

‚è±Ô∏è Complexity
Time: O(n)
Space: O(n)
